<subSubSection id="7EFD0782FF9F015689CF75EAFD9C11F9" pageId="13" pageNumber="510" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="36585409FF9F015689CF75EAFD9C11F9" blockId="13.[151,1437,259,2014]" pageId="13" pageNumber="510">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9F015689CF75EAFE9A119D" bold="true" box="[199,334,1951,1977]" pageId="13" pageNumber="510">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName id="F1E72F8AFF9F01568B3175EAFD68119D" authorityName="Wang, He &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" box="[569,700,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Odontepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="510" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrontalis">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9F01568B3175EAFD68119D" box="[569,700,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="510">latifrontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is comprised of two Latin words: “ 
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9F01568D5675EAFB40119D" box="[1118,1172,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="510">latus</emphasis>
” (wide) and “ 
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9F01568C3F75EAFAA4119D" box="[1335,1392,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="510">frons</emphasis>
”. It refers to the wide frons of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="62980481FF9C0155899F74BEFCA1116B" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4715405" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4715405" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4715405/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="511" startId="14.[151,250,1739,1763]" targetBox="[149,1439,181,1705]" targetPageId="14">
