<subSubSection id="7EFD0782FF9D015489CF72E3FC3E1765" pageId="15" pageNumber="512" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="36585409FF9D015489CF72E3FC3E1765" blockId="15.[151,1436,150,321]" pageId="15" pageNumber="512">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9D015489CF72E3FE9B1694" bold="true" box="[199,335,150,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="512">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F1E72F8AFF9D01548B7A72E2FC491694" authority="Xu &amp; He, 2006" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="2006" box="[626,925,150,177]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Odontepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusus">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9D01548B7A72E2FD3E1694" box="[626,746,150,177]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="512">O. obtusus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="527629F8FF9D01548BF872E2FC491694" author="Xu, Z. &amp; He, J." box="[752,925,150,177]" pageId="15" pageNumber="512" pagination="47 - 52" refId="ref16969" refString="Xu, Z. &amp; He, J. (2006) Three new species of the genus Odontepyris from China (Hymenoptera: Bethylidae). Entomological News, 117, 47 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.3157 / 0013 - 872 X (2006) 117 [47: TNSOTG] 2.0. CO; 2" type="journal article" year="2006">Xu &amp; He, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by vertex crest straight; metapostnotal lateral carina incomplete, first median cell of forewing oblong. However, 
<taxonomicName id="F1E72F8AFF9D01548A9372CEFB9716F0" authority="Wang &amp; He &amp; Chen, 2021" authorityName="Wang &amp; He &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" box="[923,1091,186,213]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Odontepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrontalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9D01548A9372CEFB9716F0" box="[923,1091,186,213]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="512">O. latifrontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9D01548D4572CFFB7D16F0" bold="true" box="[1101,1193,186,212]" pageId="15" pageNumber="512">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1FA03560FF9D01548D4572CFFB7D16F0" box="[1101,1193,186,212]" pageId="15" pageNumber="512" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished by having metapostnotal lateral carina extending to two-thirds of metapectal-propodeal disc, WF 3.18 × WE and dorsal pronotal area not convex, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="F1E72F8AFF9D01548B627376FD361738" authorityName="Xu &amp; He" authorityYear="2006" box="[618,738,258,285]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Odontepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="512" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obtusus">
<emphasis id="0493881BFF9D01548B627376FD361738" box="[618,738,258,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="512">O. obtusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having metapostnotal lateral carina extending to four-fifths of metapectal-propodeal disc, WF 2.92 × WE and dorsal pronotal area convex.
</paragraph>
